Package election

Class Election

  • java.lang.Object
    • election.Election
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    IRElection, OPLElection
    public class Election
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents an Election. It contains all the necessary information related to an election (such as candidates, votes, etc.) and a method to deal with tiebreakers

    • Constructor Detail

      • Election

        public Election​(java.lang.String fileName,
                java.lang.String outputPath,
                int candidateCount,
                Candidate[] candidates,
                Party[] parties,
                Ballot[] ballots,
                int seatcount)
        This is the constructor for the Election class.

        It acts a bit as a container to store all related information of an election in one spot such as candidates, parties, etc.

        Parameters:
        fileName - The name of the audit file
        outputPath - a string indicating the path we want to output media/audit files to
        candidateCount - The total number of candidates in the election
        candidates - An array containing a list of the candidates in the election
        parties - An array containing the list of parties in the election
        ballots - An array containing all ballots in the election
        seatcount - Primarily used for an OPL election, but it indicates how many seats are available in the election

      • Tiebreaker

        public Candidate Tiebreaker​(Candidate[] lizards)
        This is the tiebreaker method which occurs when there is a tie between two candidates.

        It simulates a coin flip in which the candidate that wins is randomly decided via a coin

        Parameters:
        lizards - Represents the array of current candidates left in the election
        Returns:
        The candidate that won the coin flip

      • pTiebreaker

        public Party pTiebreaker​(Party[] fun)
        This is the tiebreaker method which occurs when there is a tie between two parties.

        It simulates a coin flip in which the party that wins a seat is randomly decided via a coin

        Parameters:
        fun - Represents the array of current parties left in the election
        Returns:
        The party that won the coin flip

      • process_media

        public void process_media()
        The method to create a media file for the media. It should clearly indicate who won, who lost, and other relevant statistics.
